The winners of the GE Healthcare 2012 Cell Imaging Competition  include Jane Stout from the School of Medicine of Indiana University, in the microscopy section. Her image was in the disease focus of cancer, a Metaphase epithelial cell stained for microtubules (red), kinetochores (green) and DNA (blue).

Anushree Balachandran from Australia won first place for his image for Huntingdon’s disease stem cells.

Huntingdon’s disease becomes noticeable in mid-adult life and is the most common genetic cause of abnormal involuntary writhing movements called chorea.

